title: Suicide Rates From 1985 to 2016 in America
text:
In 2016 alone, about 12000 people aged 35 to 54 committed suicide, and about 4500 people aged 14-24 did the same thing. This project is about the Suicide rates for different ages across America have been changing over the past decades. It looks at the amount of deaths different ages have from 1985 to 2016.









You can see how different ages have higher suicide rates than other, which have been increasing and decreasing over time. like ages 35-54 are the hghest and increasing, while ages 5-14 have been stagnant.
